.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fstart-ups%2Fus-based-baron-capital-marks-up-swiggy-s-valuation-by-13-to-12-1-billion-124030800874_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fstart-ups%2Fus-based-baron-capital-marks-up-swiggy-s-valuation-by-13-to-12-1-billion-124030800874_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Over%2050%20Organisations%20Sign%20Declaration%20to%20Draw%20Attention%20to%20Climate%20Disasters%20in%20Himalayas%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F23141628%2FPauri-Garhwal.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20More%20than%2050%20social%20and%20environmental%20organisations%20mostly%20from%20India%E2%80%99s%20Himalayan%20states%20have%20signed%20the%20%E2%80%98People%20for%20Himalaya%E2%80%99%20declaration%2C%20highlighting%20the%20vulnerability%20of%20the%20mountain%20range%20to%20climate%20disasters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecent%20climate%20disasters%20are%20%E2%80%9Cpolitical%2C%20economic%20and%20social%20and%20not%20just%20environmental%E2%80%9D%20and%20cannot%20be%20called%20%E2%80%9Cnatural%20disasters%E2%80%9D%2C%20held%20the%20declaration%2C%20signed%20in%20late%20February%20by%20organisations%2C%20including%20the%20Affected%20Citizens%20of%20Teesta%20based%20in%20Sikkim%2C%20the%20Joshimath%20Bachao%20Sangharsh%20Samiti%20in%20Uttarakhand%20and%20the%20Dibang%20Resistance%20in%20Arunachal%20Pradesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20declaration%20condemned%20the%20%E2%80%9Crepression%E2%80%9D%20and%20the%20tags%20of%20%E2%80%9Canti-national%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Canti-development%E2%80%9D%20being%20labeled%20on%20people%20who%20have%20questioned%20the%20dilution%20of%20existing%20environmental%20laws%20and%20the%20non-implementation%20of%20progressive%20laws%20such%20as%20the%20forest%20rights%20act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20signatories%20vowed%20to%20work%20towards%20the%20%E2%80%9Cwell-being%20and%20sustenance%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20natural%20heritage%20of%20the%20Himalayas%20and%20support%20the%20sustainability-oriented%20decentralised%20governance%20%E2%80%94%20backed%20by%20science%20and%20indigenous%20knowledge%20%E2%80%94%20of%20the%20Himalayas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20declaration%20comes%20at%20a%20time%20when%20several%20states%20across%20the%20mountain%20range%20have%20witnessed%20numerous%20disasters%20in%20recent%20times%20(including%2C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fsikkim-glof-triggered-flood-in-teesta-because-warnings-remained-neglected%5C%22%3E%20glacial%20lake%20outburst%20floods%20GLOF%3C%2Fa%3E%20such%20as%20that%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fdam-site-completely-devastated-loss-assessment-sikkim-disaster-time%5C%22%3ESouth%20Lhonak%20Lake%20in%20Sikkim%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20October%20last%20year)%2C%20which%20have%20claimed%20peoples%E2%80%99%20lives%20and%20caused%20much%20ecological%20and%20environmental%20destruction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInvestigations%20into%20some%20of%20these%20incidents%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fsikkim-disaster-vimal-khawas-interview-himalaya%5C%22%3Erevealed%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20authorities%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fdam-site-completely-devastated-loss-assessment-sikkim-disaster-time%5C%22%3Edid%20not%20follow%3C%2Fa%3E%20existing%20rules%20for%20developmental%20activities%20in%20the%20areas%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fsikkim-glof-triggered-flood-in-teesta-because-warnings-remained-neglected%5C%22%3Eignored%20the%20fears%20and%20concerns%3C%2Fa%3E%20raised%20by%20experts%20and%20local%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20studies%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fpii%2FS0169555X21001914%5C%22%3Eone%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202021%20that%20mapped%20the%20impacts%20of%20a%20GLOF%20in%20South%20Lhonak%20lake%20predicted%20that%20settlements%20downstream%20were%20at%20high%20risk%20of%20flooding.%20But%20despite%20this%2C%20people%20downstream%20did%20not%20receive%20early%20warning%20systems%2C%20if%20they%20had%2C%20several%20lives%20could%20have%20been%20saved%2C%20experts%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fdam-site-completely-devastated-loss-assessment-sikkim-disaster-time%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fa-himalayan-tragedy-foretold%5C%22%3EA%20Himalayan%20Tragedy%20Foretold%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20February%2027%20and%2028%2C%20representatives%20of%20social%2C%20rights%20and%20environmental%20organisations%20across%20several%20Himalayan%20states%20came%20together%20to%20talk%20about%20the%20Himalayas%2C%20disasters%20and%20people.%20The%20event%20was%20also%20attended%20by%20climate%20scientists%2C%20as%20per%20a%20press%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20representatives%20of%20the%20organisations%20put%20together%20the%20%E2%80%98People%20for%20Himalaya%E2%80%99%20campaign%20declaration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Climate%20disasters%20are%20not%20just%20environmental%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20declaration%2C%20the%20disasters%20now%20seen%20in%20the%20natural%20environment%20are%20%E2%80%9Csystemic%20and%20policy-induced%20disasters%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20the%20%E2%80%9Cresult%20of%20historical%20processes%20of%20exploitation%20and%20governance%20failure%20at%20various%20levels%20%E2%80%93%20from%20global%20to%20local%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThus%20these%20disasters%20are%20political%2C%20economic%20and%20social%2C%20not%20just%20environmental%20disasters.%20We%20refuse%20to%20call%20them%20%E2%80%98natural%E2%80%99%20disasters.%20We%20understand%20that%20those%20who%20are%20the%20least%20responsible%20for%20these%20disasters%20are%20in%20fact%20the%20worst%20impacted%20by%20these%20disasters%20%E2%80%93%20and%20have%20been%20further%20rendered%20powerless%20and%20resource%20less%20in%20the%20process%20of%20disaster-making.%20These%20include%20marginal%20farmers%2C%20landless%20dalits%2C%20forest%20dwellers%2C%20adivasis%2C%20women%2C%20migrant%20workers%2C%20pastoralists%2C%20minorities%2C%20persons%20with%20disabilities%20and%20those%20living%20in%20conflict%20zones%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20declaration%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThose%20who%20are%20the%20most%20responsible%20for%20the%20climate%20disasters%20that%20the%20Himalaya%20are%20witnessing%20%E2%80%9Care%20those%20in%20power%20and%20extracting%20resources%20for%20profiteering%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20declaration%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20held%20several%20groups%20of%20people%20accountable%20for%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20growing%20commodification%20of%20the%20Himalaya%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20from%20financial%20institutions%20of%20the%20global%20north%2C%20to%20the%20national%20and%20state%20governments%20and%20governance%20institutions%2C%20corporates%20and%20contractors.%20In%20the%20last%20few%20decades%2C%20%E2%80%9Ccapitalist%20greed%20in%20the%20name%20of%20development%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20in%20the%20form%20of%20mega%20dams%20and%20four-lane%20highways%2C%20railway%20projects%2C%20commercial%20tourism%20and%20urbanisation%20%E2%80%93%20has%20been%20an%20issue%2C%20the%20declaration%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFor%20sustainable%20development%20and%20climate%20justice%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20these%20land%20use%20changes%20have%20damaged%20the%20rivers%2C%20forests%2C%20grasslands%20and%20mountains%20of%20the%20region%2C%20it%20has%20also%20destroyed%20local%20livelihoods%20and%20replaced%20them%20with%20%E2%80%9Ctop-down%2C%20market%20dependent%20and%20techno-managerial%20solutions%20implemented%20through%20international%20loans%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20declaration%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20declaration%20also%20stated%20that%20over%20the%20last%2015%20years%2C%20several%20environmental%20laws%20and%20regulatory%20or%20protective%20policies%20have%20been%20%E2%80%9Cdiluted%20or%20eliminated%20in%20the%20name%20of%20national%20security%2C%20national%20interest%20and%20%E2%80%98green%E2%80%99%20growth%20endangering%20our%20ecology%20and%20putting%20under%20threat%20the%20very%20survival%20of%20our%20people.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20progressive%20laws%20for%20land%20allocation%2C%20housing%20rights%2C%20forest%20rights%2C%20rehabilitation%20and%20relocation%20of%20development%2Fdisaster%20affected%20people%20and%20labour%20laws%20stand%20non-implemented%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20condemn%20the%20repression%20of%20voices%20who%20have%20questioned%20this%20mindless%20destruction%20and%20the%20use%20of%20labels%20as%20anti-national%20and%20anti-development%20to%20create%20false%20narratives.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fsikkim-disaster-vimal-khawas-interview-himalaya%5C%22%3EHuman%20Failure%20One%20of%20Many%20Reasons%20for%20Sikkim%20Disaster%3B%20Lots%20of%20Work%2C%20Planning%20Ahead%3A%20Local%20Scientist%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20declaration%2C%20the%20%E2%80%98People%20for%20Himalaya%E2%80%99%20campaign%20will%20work%20for%20the%20%E2%80%9Cwellbeing%20and%20sustenance%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20Himalayan%20natural%20heritage%2C%20ranging%20from%20glaciers%20and%20rivers%20to%20alpine%20pastures%2C%20forests%20and%20the%20diverse%20inhabitants%20whose%20identity%20and%20survival%20depend%20on%20the%20Himalaya.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20stand%20in%20alliance%20with%20organisations%20that%20support%20and%20advocate%20for%20democratic%20and%20decentralised%20governance%20in%20the%20Himalaya%20based%20on%20the%20principles%20of%20sustainability%20guided%20by%20balancing%20science%20and%20indigenous%20knowledge%3B%20gender%2C%20caste%2C%20ethnic%20and%20intergenerational%20equity%3B%20and%20climate%20justice%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20declaration%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOrganisations%20that%20are%20signatories%20to%20the%20declaration%20include%20Himachal%20Pradesh%E2%80%99s%20Himdhara%20Collective%3B%20National%20Alliance%20for%20People%E2%80%99s%20Movements%2C%20India%3B%20Sikkim%E2%80%99s%20Council%20for%20Civic%20Democratic%20Engagement%3B%20South%20Asia%20Network%20on%20Dams%2C%20Rivers%20and%20People%20and%20the%20Appiko-Chipko%20movement%20of%20Karnataka%2C%20to%20name%20a%20few.%20Uttarakhand%E2%80%99s%20Joshimath%20Bachao%20Sangharsh%20Samiti%20%E2%80%93%20which%20first%20raised%20the%20concerns%20regarding%20land%20subsidence%20in%20the%20town%20of%20Joshimath%20that%20drew%20national%20attention%20%E2%80%93%20is%20also%20a%20signatory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CDuring%20the%20two-day%20dialogue%20in%20Himachal%20the%20experience%20from%20all%20the%20Himalayan%20region%20was%20that%20in%20case%20of%20extreme%20events%20post-disaster%20support%20from%20the%20centre%20has%20been%20inadequate%20and%20restricted%20to%20relief%20with%20no%20attention%20to%20or%20support%20for%20prevention%20and%20rehabilitation%2C%E2%80%9D%20noted%20the%20Climate%20Front%20Jammu%2C%20in%20a%20press%20statement%20released%20on%20March%207.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20press%20release%2C%20the%20Jammu-based%20organisation%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20also%20a%20signatory%20of%20the%20declaration%20%E2%80%94%20underlined%20how%20the%20union%20government%20ignored%20repeated%20requests%20from%20Sikkim%20and%20Himachal%20Pradesh%20to%20declare%20the%20disasters%20faced%20by%20their%20states%20in%202023%20as%20%E2%80%98national%20disasters%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20little%20place%20for%20people%20%E2%80