ter%20a%20few%20months%2C%20she%20was%20moved%20to%20a%20homeless%20shelter%20by%20police.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20staff%20at%20the%20shelter%20said%20initially%20she%20was%20in%20shock%20and%20incoherent.%20When%20interviewed%20by%20this%20researcher%2C%20not%20once%20did%20she%20blame%20her%20son%20for%20anything.%20She%20just%20repeated%3A%20%E2%80%9CI%20was%20destined%20to%20be%20here.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20another%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Frajkot-professor-throws-ailing-mother-off-terrace-booked-5013435%2F).%5C%22%3Ecase%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20man%20confessed%20to%20throwing%20his%2064-year-old%20mother%20off%20the%20terrace%20of%20their%20home%20as%20she%20was%20ill%20and%20a%20burden.%20His%20mother%20later%20died.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20abandonment%20and%20disregard%20for%20older%20women%20is%20all%20too%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flink.springer.com%2Freferenceworkentry%2F10.1007%2F978-981-16-1914-4_13-1%5C%22%3Ecommon%20%3C%2Fa%3Ein%20a%20country%20like%20India%20where%20filial%20piety%20is%20upheld%20as%20a%20virtue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAge%20compounds%20the%20hardships%20of%20many%20older%20women%20in%20a%20society%20marked%20by%20gender%20inequality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOlder%20women%20face%20additional%20challenges%20of%20financial%20insecurity%2C%20destitution%20and%20health%20challenges%20related%20to%20ageing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20neoliberal%20society%2C%20people%20are%20valued%20for%20their%20economic%20contribution.%20A%20similar%20logic%20operates%20in%20many%20Indian%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20an%20older%20family%20member%20is%20not%20earning%20an%20income%2C%20they%20are%20deemed%20to%20be%20dependents%20and%20a%20%E2%80%98burden%E2%80%99.%20Patriarchal%20cultural%20norms%20relegate%20women%20to%20domestic%20duties.%20Many%20women%20remain%20unemployed%20throughout%20their%20lives%2C%20and%20a%20majority%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.helpageindia.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2FWomen-Ageing-Invisible-or-Empowered-a-HelpAge-India-2023-report.pdf%5C%22%3Edo%20not%20own%20assets%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20creates%20economic%20hardships%20in%20late%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%202015%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.agewellfoundation.org%2Fpdf%2Freports%2FGENDER%2520DISCRIMINATION%2520AMONG%2520OLDER%2520WOMEN%2520IN%2520INDIA.pdf%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20older%20women%20have%20a%20diminished%20status%20in%20the%20family%20because%20they%20do%20not%20earn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1080%2F13600810601045833%3Ftab%3Dpermissions%26scroll%3Dtop%5C%22%3Eeven%20though%3C%2Fa%3E%20they%20contribute%20to%20their%20children%E2%80%99s%20families%20by%20being%20caregivers%20for%20grandchildren.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20care%20work%20in%20the%20family%20remains%20highly%20devalued.%20Along%20with%20this%2C%20the%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findia.unfpa.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fpub-pdf%2F20230926_india_ageing_report_2023_web_version_.pdf)%5C%22%3Efeminisation%20of%20ageing%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%98%20as%20evidenced%20by%20the%20increased%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcensusindia.gov.in%2Fnada%2Findex.php%2Fcatalog%2F43473%5C%22%3Elife%20expectancy%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20women%20(compared%20to%20men)%20implies%20that%20older%20women%20will%20continue%20to%20be%20dependent%20on%20others%20for%20prolonged%20periods.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeing%20dependent%20on%20kin%20can%20exacerbate%20vulnerabilities.%20My%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flink.springer.com%2Fchapter%2F10.1007%2F978-981-10-3439-8_3%5C%22%3Eresearch%20%3C%2Fa%3Eshows%20that%20older%20women%20could%20be%20easy%20targets%20of%20coercion%20and%20manipulation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20case%20of%20propertied%20older%20women%2C%20many%20experience%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Fmaharashtra%2Fmany-elderly-not-being-looked-after-withering-joint-family-system-to-blamemumbai-high-court-2870735%5C%22%3Eabuse%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20transferring%20property%20to%20their%20adult%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20many%20women%20in%20the%20country%20do%20not%20own%20property%20despite%20there%20being%20laws%20which%20grant%20property%20rights%20to%20women.%20Such%20women%20are%20sometimes%20driven%20to%20destitution%2C%20and%20many%20are%20abandoned%20by%20family%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOlder%20women%20can%20claim%20maintenance%20from%20family%20members%20under%20existing%20legal%20provisions%20in%20India.%20Section%2019%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fbitstream%2F123456789%2F1638%2F1%2FAA1956____78.pdf%5C%22%3EHindu%20Adoptions%20and%20Maintenance%20Act%2C%201956%3C%2Fa%3E%20allows%20a%20widow%20(who%20does%20not%20remarry)%20to%20claim%20maintenance%20from%20the%20legal%20heirs%20of%20the%20deceased%20who%20share%20the%20property%20of%20the%20deceased.%20Widows%20can%20also%20claim%20maintenance%20under%20Section%20125%20of%20the%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure%20from%20their%20children%2C%20unconditionally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fbitstream%2F123456789%2F6831%2F1%2Fmaintenance_and_welfare_of_parents_and_senior_citizens_act.pdf%5C%22%3EThe%20Maintenance%20and%20Welfare%20of%20Parents%20and%20Senior%20Citizens%20Act%2C%202007%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20MW%20Act%2C%20was%20formulated%20especially%20for%20senior%20citizens%E2%80%99%20welfare.%20Section%204%20obligates%20sons%2C%20daughters%2C%20grandchildren%20who%20are%20not%20minors%20and%20any%20legal%20heir%20of%20her%20property%20to%20provide%20maintenance.%20This%20law%20defines%20maintenance%20as%20food%2C%20clothing%2C%20shelter%20and%20medical%20treatment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELegal%20safeguards%20against%20abandonment%2C%20usurpation%20of%20property%20and%20abuse%20exist%20in%20the%20MW%20Act%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fhandle%2F123456789%2F2021%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAn%2520Act%2520to%2520provide%2520for%2Cconnected%2520therewith%2520or%2520incidental%2520thereto.%26amp%3Btext%3DNotification%253A%2CS.O.%5C%22%3EProtection%20of%20Women%20from%20Domestic%20Violence%20Act%2C%202005%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20existing%20laws%2C%20however%2C%20do%20not%20particularly%20address%20the%20discrimination%20faced%20by%20some%20older%20women%20such%20as%20childless%2C%20unmarried%20or%20trans%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsansad.in%2FgetFile%2FBillsTexts%2FLSBillTexts%2FAsintroduced%2F161%2520OF%25202022%2520AS.pdf%3Fsource%3Dlegislation%5C%22%3EProtection%20of%20Rights%20of%20Widows%20and%20Single%20Women%20and%20Abolishment%20of%20Widowhood%20Practices%20Bill%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20introduced%20in%202022%20but%20nothing%20came%20of%20it.%20Destigmatising%20widowhood%20and%20singlehood%20and%20restoring%20dignity%20to%20those%20belonging%20to%20sexual%20minorities%20is%20crucial%20for%20empowering%20older%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20laws%20undoubtedly%20safeguard%20the%20rights%20of%20older%20women%2C%20it%20is%20impractical%20to%20conjure%20a%20law%20for%20every%20situation%20of%20harm%20done%20to%20older%20women%3B%20rather%20there%20is%20a%20need%20to%20proactively%20implement%20existing%20laws.%20As%20political%20theorist%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fonlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1111%2F1467-8675.00183%5C%22%3EWendy%20Brown%3C%2Fa%3E%20argues%2C%20%E2%80%98%E2%80%A6rights%E2%80%A6serve%20as%20a%20mitigation%20%E2%80%94%20but%20not%20a%20resolution%20%E2%80%94%20of%20subordinating%20powers.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPatriarchal%20ideas%20that%20prevent%20women%20from%20pursuing%20a%20life%20of%20one%E2%80%99s%20own%20choice%20must%20be%20questioned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20women%20remain%20engaged%20in%20care%20work%20throughout%20their%20lives.%20A%20woman%20at%20a%20charitable%20care%20home%20in%20Kolkata%20said%20%E2%80%98she%20found%20herself%E2%80%99%20after%20relocating%20to%20the%20care%20home%20after%20her%20spouse%E2%80%99s%20death.%20She%20was%20relieved%20of%20the%20care%20work%20and%20now%20she%20was%20%E2%80%98free.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECare%20work%20must%20be%20accorded%20due%20importance%20in%20the%20political%20discourse.%20Restoring%20dignity%20in%20women%E2%80%99s%20labour%20and%20building%20a%20supportive%20environment%20for%20women%20to%20perform%20their%20caring%20duties%20often%20determines%20their%20wellbeing%20in%20late%20life.%20Many%20women%20combat%20loneliness.%20More%20recreation%20facilities%20in%20the%20neighbourhood%20can%20be%20made%20available.%20Age-appropriate%20occupations%20can%20be%20considered%20for%20women%20to%20enhance%20financial%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEnsuring%20safety%2C%20access%20to%20helplines%20and%20counselling%20support%2C%20access%20to%20inexpensive%20medical%20care%2C%20palliative%20care%2C%20dementia%20care%2C%20affordable%20permanent%20housing%2C%20and%20financial%20security%20through%20pension%20schemes%20are%20areas%20where%20attention%20needs%20to%20be%20given.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20common%20concern%20of%20many%20older%20women%20living%20in%20cities%2C%20as%20per%20my%20research%2C%20has%20been%20sourcing%20essentials%20and%20recruiting%20reliable%20care%20workers%20for%20themselves.%20Crimes%20against%20older%20women%20in%20cities%20such%20as%20murder%2C%20robbery%20and%20assault%20are%20often%20reported%20especially%20in%20metropolitan%20cities%20like%20Mumbai%2C%20Delhi%20and%20Kolkata.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20older%20women%20interviewed%20mentioned%20how%20they%20would%20prefer%20shifting%20to%20institutional%20care%20rather%20than%20relying%20on%20paid%20domestic%20workers%20and%20%3Ci%3Eayahs%3C%2Fi%3E.%20This%20also%20highlights%20the%20need%20to%20have%20more%20care%20homes%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20state%2C%20community%2C%20as%20well%20as%20regulated%20market%20intervention%20in%20the%20above%20domains%2C%20is%20key%20to%20providing%20a%20conducive%20environment%20for%20older%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98Older%20women%E2%80%99%20is%20not%20a%20homogenous%20category.%20Therefore%2C%20identifying%20unique%20needs%20based%20on%20their%20context%20is%20also%20crucial%20to%20meet%20the%20goals%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.who.int%2Fmedia%2Fdocs%2Fdefault-source%2Fdecade-of-healthy-ageing%2Fdecade-proposal-final-apr2020-en.pdf%5C%22%3EUN%20Decade%20of%20Healthy%20Ageing%3C%2Fa%3E%20(2021-2030).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EDr.%20Deblina%20Dey%20is%20Associate%20Professor%20of%20Sociology%20%26amp%3B%20Assistant%20Director%20of%20the%20Centre%20for%20Law%20%26amp%3B%20Humanities%20at%20the%20Law%20School%2C%20O.P.%20Jindal%20Global%20University.%20She%20is%20pursuing%20her%20postdoctoral%20research%20on%20care%20interventions%20for%20older%20people%20in%20urban%20India.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EOriginally%20published%20under%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcreativecommons.org%2Flicenses%2Fby%2F4.0%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3ECreative%20Commons%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%20by%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F360info.org%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E360info%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%E2%84%A2.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709902815000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F08173620%2Fimage-1924.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fabused-abandoned-neglected-the-plight-of-indias-older-women%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Restoring%20dignity%20in%20women%E2%80%99s%20labour%20can%20give%20older%20women%20the%20care%20and%20respect%20they%20deserve%20in%20late%20life.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fabused-abandoned-neglected-the-plight-of-indias-older-women%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7