5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20marks%20a%20wider%20gender%20gap%20compared%20to%20the%20previous%20year%2C%20with%20women%20facing%20challenges%20in%20heading%20crucial%20board%20committees%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20gender%20disparity%20extends%20to%20board%20committees%2C%20where%20women%20find%20themselves%20in%20the%20minority%2C%20holding%20approximately%2014%25%20of%20positions%20in%20risk%20management%20and%20over%2020%25%20in%20the%20nomination%20and%20remuneration%20committee.%20Meanwhile%20men%20occupy%20around%20eight%20out%20of%2010%20board%20committee%20positions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20a%20large%20number%20of%20board%20rooms%20are%20due%20for%20a%20shuffle%20this%20year%20as%20The%20Companies%20Act%2C%20which%20came%20into%20force%20in%202014%2C%20mandates%20a%2010-year%20term%20for%20independent%20directors.%20This%20means%20as%20companies%20refresh%20their%20boards%20this%20year%2C%20they%20will%20have%20an%20opportunity%20to%20achieve%20at%20least%2030%25%20representation%20of%20women%20in%20boardrooms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithout%20this%2C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findustry%2Fnews%2Finternational-women-s-day-public-private-gap-widens-on-women-directors-124030701035_1.html%5C%22%3E%20the%20target%20of%2030%25%20gender%20diversity%20in%20the%20boardroom%20will%20only%20be%20met%20by%202058%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20current%20pace%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20might%20see%20an%20uptick%20as%20a%20consequence.%20While%20it%20is%20important%20to%20look%20at%20women%E2%80%99s%20representation%20across%20the%20board%2C%20another%20metric%20would%20be%20to%20look%20at%20women%20in%20the%20workforce.%20This%20indicator%20would%20be%20helpful%20to%20understand%20gender%20diversity%20at%20a%20broader%20level%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20for%20the%20company%2C%20but%20the%20economy%2C%E2%80%9D%20Amit%20Tandon%2C%20founder%20and%20managing%20director%20of%20IiAS%20told%20%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Standard%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20data%20from%20the%20Centre%20for%20Monitoring%20Indian%20Economy%2C%20only%2011.1%25%20of%20working-age%20Indian%20women%20were%20employed%20or%20seeking%20employment%20as%20of%20February%202024%2C%20compared%20to%20a%2068.1%25%20labor%20force%20participation%20rate%20for%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20data%20from%20Deloitte%20Global%20Boardroom%20Program%E2%80%99s%20Women%20in%20the%20Boardroom%20report%20shows%20that%20only%205.1%25%20of%20the%20CEOs%20in%20the%20400%20listed%20companies%20on%20the%20MSCI%20index%20are%20women.%20This%20figure%20stood%20at%203.4%25%20in%202018%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fjobs%2Fc-suite%2Fcos-talk-up-diversity-but-boards-stay-stubbornly-male-with-needle-barely-moving-in-6-yrs-survey%2Farticleshow%2F108309038.cms%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20also%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20400%20companies%20have%20a%20total%20of%20524%20women%20directors.%20This%20includes%20those%20companies%20that%20only%20fulfil%20the%20condition%20of%20having%20one%20woman%20director%2C%20implying%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20just%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fjobs%2Fc-suite%2Fcos-talk-up-diversity-but-boards-stay-stubbornly-male-with-needle-barely-moving-in-6-yrs-survey%2Farticleshow%2F108309038.cms%5C%22%3Ea%20ticking-the-box%20exercise%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COrganisations%20have%20to%20address%20the%20issue%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20pyramid%20by%20including%20equal%20number%20of%20women%20right%20at%20the%20fresher%20level%2C%E2%80%9D%20Wipro%20chief%20financial%20officer%20Aparna%20Iyer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fjobs%2Fc-suite%2Fcos-talk-up-diversity-but-boards-stay-stubbornly-male-with-needle-barely-moving-in-6-yrs-survey%2Farticleshow%2F108309038.cms%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20%3Cem%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThen%20they%20have%20to%20retain%20the%20women%20through%20their%20toughest%20and%20key%20life%20stages%20such%20as%20maternity%20and%20care%20giving.%20It%20is%20crucial%20then%20that%20organisations%20proactively%20build%20a%20robust%20leadership%20pipeline%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709895624000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F08151835%2Fboard-room-unsplash_resize.jpg.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fdespite-talk-of-diversity-women-still-a-minority-in-indian-boardrooms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22According%20to%20data%20from%20primeinfobase.com%2C%20a%20mere%2019%25%20of%20total%20directorships%20are%20held%20by%20women%20in%20the%20private%20sector%20while%2014.3%25%20in%20the%20public%20sector%20for%20Nifty%20500%20companies%2C%20as%20of%20March%206.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fdespite-talk-of-diversity-women-still-a-minority-in-indian-boardrooms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Amitav%20Ghosh%20Wins%20Erasmus%20Prize%202024%20for%20His%20Writings%20on%20Climate%20Change%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2016%2F05%2FAmitav_Ghosh_-_River_Of_Smoke_3.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Indian%20writer%20Amitav%20Ghosh%20is%20the%20winner%20of%20this%20year%E2%80%99s%20Erasmus%20Prize%2C%20for%20his%20writings%20on%20the%20planetary%20crisis%20and%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Praemium%20Erasmianum%20Foundation%20in%20the%20Netherlands%20awards%20the%20prize%20annually%20for%20an%20organisation%20or%20individual%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cexceptional%20contributions%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20fields%20of%20the%20humanities%2C%20social%20sciences%20or%20arts%20in%20Europe%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20March%207%2C%20Ghosh%20posted%20on%20social%20media%20that%20it%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Cdelight%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Chonour%E2%80%9D%20to%20be%20conferred%20the%20award.%20He%20will%20receive%20the%20award%20in%20person%20in%20the%20Netherlands%20in%20November.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20Ghosh%E2%80%99s%20works%20including%20%3Ci%3EThe%20Great%20Derangement%3C%2Fi%3E%20and%20%3Ci%3EThe%20Nutmeg%E2%80%99s%20Curse%3C%2Fi%3E%20dwell%20on%20the%20ongoing%20planetary%20crisis%20and%20are%20interlinked%20with%20the%20impacts%20of%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ERecurring%20themes%20of%20nature%2C%20people%2C%20and%20climate%20change%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENature%2C%20people%2C%20and%20interactions%20between%20both%2C%20have%20been%20major%20themes%20in%20several%20of%20Ghosh%E2%80%99s%20works%20%E2%80%93%20from%20some%20parts%20in%20his%20fictional%20Ibis%20trilogy%20(%3Ci%3ESea%20of%20Poppies%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%20%3Ci%3ERiver%20of%20Smoke%3C%2Fi%3E%20and%20%3Ci%3EFlood%20of%20Fire%3C%2Fi%3E)%20to%20%3Ci%3EThe%20Hungry%20Tide%3C%2Fi%3E.%20The%20latter%20%E2%80%93%20published%2020%20years%20ago%20%E2%80%93%20dwells%20on%20the%20story%20of%20a%20marine%20biologist%20in%20search%20of%20the%20rare%20Irrawady%20dolphin%20in%20the%20Sunderbans.%20Set%20against%20the%20backdrop%20of%20climate%20change%20and%20a%20cyclone%20that%20changes%20the%20protagonists%E2%80%99%20lives%2C%20the%20book%20also%20touched%20on%20man-animal%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20of%20Ghosh%E2%80%99s%20books%2C%20%3Ci%3EThe%20Great%20Derangement%3A%20Climate%20Change%20and%20the%20Unthinkable%3C%2Fi%3E%20(2016)%20is%20a%20non-fictional%20work%20that%20touches%20on%20colonialism%20and%20the%20politics%20interlinked%20with%20climate%20change%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20art%20of%20writing%20about%20the%20issue.%20In%20his%20latest%20book%20%3Ci%3EThe%20Nutmeg%E2%80%99s%20Curse%3C%2Fi%3E%20%E2%80%93%20written%20during%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20%E2%80%93%20Ghosh%20explores%20the%20exploitation%20of%20indigenous%20communities%2C%20ownership%20of%20natural%20resources%20and%20their%20use%2C%20along%20with%20climate%20change%20and%20colonialism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%E2%80%98Imagining%20the%20unthinkable%E2%80%99%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHe%20receives%20the%20prize%20for%20his%20passionate%20contribution%20to%20the%20theme%20%E2%80%98imagining%20the%20unthinkable%E2%80%99%2C%20in%20which%20an%20unprecedented%20global%20crisis%20%E2%80%93%20climate%20change%20%E2%80%93%20takes%20shape%20through%20the%20written%20word%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20Praemium%20Erasmianum%20Foundation%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ferasmusprijs.org%2Fen%2Flaureates%2Famitav-ghosh%2F%5C%22%3Epress%20release%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CGhosh%20has%20delved%20deeply%20into%20the%20question%20of%20how%20to%20do%20justice%20to%20this%20existential%20threat%20that%20defies%20our%20imagination.%20His%20work%20offers%20a%20remedy%20by%20making%20an%20uncertain%20future%20palpable%20through%20compelling%20stories%20about%20the%20past.%20He%20also%20wields%20his%20pen%20to%20show%20that%20the%20climate%20crisis%20is%20a%20cultural%20crisis%20that%20results%20from%20a%20dearth%20of%20the%20imagination%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGhosh%20expressed%20his%20%E2%80%9Cdelight%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Chonour%E2%80%9D%20on%20the%20award%20on%20March%207%2C%20via%20a%20post%20on%20the%20social%20media%20platform%20X%2C%20formerly%20Twitter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20an%20incredible%20privilege%20to%20follow%20in%20the%20footsteps%20of%20legends%20like%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FTrevornoah%5C%22%3E%20%40Trevornoah%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20A.S.%20Byatt%20and%20Barbara%20Ehrenreich%2C%E2%80%9D%20Ghosh%20tweeted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3ESo%20this%20just%20happened%E2%80%A6%20needless%20to%20say%2C%20I%20am%20delighted%20and%20hugely%20honored!%20It%E2%80%99s%20an%20incredible%20privilege%20to%20follow%20in%20the%20footsteps%20of%20legends%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FTrevornoah%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40Trevornoah%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20A.S.%20Byatt%20and%20Barbara%20Ehrenreich.%20More%20here%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FNIxzxQbqcy%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FNIxzxQbqcy%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2F4eIQJfz2Jq%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2F4eIQJfz2Jq%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Amitav%20Ghosh%20(%40GhoshAmitav)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FGhoshAmitav%2Fstatus%2F1765733029006176673%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EMarch%207%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20the%20prize%20went%20to%20South%20African%20comedian%20Trevor%20Noah.%20Past%20recipients%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ferasmusprijs.org%2Fen%2Flaureates%2F%5C%22%3Einclude%3C%2Fa%3E%20American%20journalist%20and%20writer%20Barbara%20Ehrenreich%20(2018)%2C%20writer%20A.S.%20Byatt%20(2016)%20and%20Charles%20Chaplin%20and%20Ingmar%20Bergman%20in%201965.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709895245000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Famitav-ghosh-wins-erasmus-prize-2024-for-his-writings-on-climate-change%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Many%20of%20Ghosh%E2%80%99s%20works%20including%20'The%20Great%20Derangement'%20and%20'The%20Nutmeg%E2%80%99s%20Curse'%20dwell%20on%20the%20ongoing%20planetary%20crisis%20and%20the%20impacts%20of%20climate%20change%C2%A0%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Famitav-ghosh-wins-erasmus-prize-2024-for-his-writings-on-climate-change%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22