0by%20temporal%20reasons%20of%20increased%20revenue-share%2C%20came%20at%20a%20huge%20price%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20true%20spirit%20of%20democratic%20federalism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20any%20voting%20exercise%20within%20the%20GST%20Council%2C%20the%20Centre%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fexplained-voting-at-the-gst-council-6206947%2F%5C%22%3Ecarries%20a%20weight%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20one-third%20(33.33%25)%2C%20with%20the%20balance%20two-thirds%20(66.67%25)%20shared%20by%20the%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20for%20a%20proposal%20to%20be%20approved%2C%20it%20needs%20the%20support%20of%2075%25%20of%20the%20total%20voting%20weight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP%20is%20now%20in%20power%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Felections%2Fstory%2Fbjp-political-map-landscape-after-latest-win-assembly-elections-congress-india-electoral-map-and-road-to-2024-lok-sabha-elections-2471578-2023-12-04%5C%22%3E12%20of%20the%2028%20states%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20India%20and%20is%20in%20the%20ruling%20coalition%20in%20four%20others.%20And%20in%20December%202019%2C%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Fend-of-consensus-as-gst-council-takes-voting-route%2Fstory-NFhpsIUG2aO1yysQA1JkfJ.html%5C%22%3Ehad%20shifted%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20voting%20from%20its%20tradition%20of%20taking%20consensus-based%20decisions%20to%20settle%20all%20matters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20state%20governments%20have%20also%20lost%20their%20ability%20to%20independently%20collect%20revenue%20from%20the%20sales%20tax.%20Additionally%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20trend%20towards%20centralisation%20of%20power%20in%20politics%2C%20which%20could%20reduce%20states%E2%80%99%20ability%20to%20find%20new%20revenue%20sources%20or%20borrow%20money%20for%20their%20expenses%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEach%20of%20these%20issues%20merit%20wider%20attention%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20upcoming%20general%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20the%20aggrieved%20states%E2%80%99%20perspective%2C%20there%20are%20three%20key%20principles%20that%20can%20ensure%20a%20better%20partnership%20based%20on%20trust%20and%20a%20more%20robust%20federal-finance%20relationship%20between%20the%20Centre%20and%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Famid-indias-silent-fiscal-crisis-and-fragile-federalism-16th-finance-commission-has-an-uphill-task%5C%22%3EAmid%20India%E2%80%99s%20Silent%20Fiscal%20Crisis%20and%20Fragile%20Federalism%2C%2016th%20Finance%20Commission%20Has%20an%20Uphill%20Task%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVertical%20equity%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20principle%20of%20vertical%20equity%20in%20public%20finance%20entrusts%20a%20government%20to%20ask%20those%20who%20earn%20more%20or%20have%20a%20higher%20wealth%20to%20pay%20more%20in%20their%20share%20of%20contributed%20revenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20a%20complex%20system%20of%20intergovernmental%20fiscal%20relations.%20This%20complexity%20has%20its%20roots%20in%20a%20number%20of%20factors%2C%20including%20ethnic%2C%20social%2C%20and%20economic%20disparities%20among%20states%2Fregions%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20long-standing%20vertical-imbalance%20between%20the%20expenditure%20and%20revenue%20raising%20responsibilities%20of%20the%20state%20governments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20imbalance%20in%20the%20past%20was%20covered%20by%20revenue-sharing%20arrangements%2C%20in%20which%20states%2C%20particularly%20developing%20states%2C%20received%20a%20variety%20of%20grants%20from%20the%20Centre.%20Even%20if%20grants%20are%20not%20allocated%2C%20the%20Centre%20can%20do%20more%20in%20reducing%20the%20cesses%2Fsurcharge%20composition%20in%20the%20macro-tax%20weightage%2C%20while%20imposing%20a%20larger%20share%20of%20direct%20tax%20burden%20on%20the%20top%2010%25%20of%20the%20wealth-asset%20endowed%20class%2C%20safeguarding%20a%20larger%20devolved%20proportion%20of%20that%20%E2%80%98tax%E2%80%99%20revenue%20for%20states%2C%20that%20need%20additional%20resources.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20author%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fconsumption-based-tax-system-reform-india%5C%22%3Ehad%20earlier%20discussed%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20proposal%20to%20levy%20a%20%E2%80%98consumption%20tax%E2%80%99%20on%20the%20richer%20(top%2010%25)%20asset%20class%2C%20consuming%20a%20larger%20proportion%20of%20luxury%20goods%2C%20that%20can%20help%20them%20pay%20more%20as%20compared%20to%20other%20classes%20who%20pay%20a%20similar%20amount%20of%20tax%20(in%20case%20of%20GST%20or%20other%20indirectly%20imposed%20tax)%20irrespective%20of%20the%20income%20they%20earn%20or%20the%20wealth%20they%20endow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EProportionality%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProportionality%2C%20in%20a%20jurisprudence%20sense%20of%20public%20law%20and%20political%20theory%2C%20appeals%20to%20%E2%80%98reason%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98reasonable%E2%80%99%20conduct%20for%20the%20way%20a%20court%20sentences%20a%20convict%2C%20or%20how%20a%20parliamentary%20body%20or%20executive%20may%20choose%20to%20function.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20cannot%20(or%20shouldn%E2%80%99t)%20use%20a%20cannon%20to%20fire%20a%20sparrow.%20Balancing%20means%20with%20ends%20matters.%20The%20Finance%20Commission%20has%20a%20mandate%20in%20recommending%20ways%20for%20the%20central%20government%20to%20be%20more%20reasonable%20and%20proportionate%20in%20the%20way%20they%20organise%20their%20devolution%20framework%20with%20the%20states%20in%20a%20time-sensitive%20and%20needs-based%20manner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20time%20when%20the%20federal%20faith%20and%20mutual%20trust%20in%20the%20Centre-state%20relations%20have%20taken%20a%20more%20%E2%80%98uncooperative%E2%80%99%20turn%2C%20largely%20due%20to%20political%20factors%2C%20it%20would%20be%20interesting%20to%20see%20how%20the%20new%2016th%20Finance%20Commission%20handles%20this%20growing%20friction%20back%20to%20its%20original%20charter%3A%20of%20ensuring%20%E2%80%98pooled%20sovereignty%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20truest%20sense.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJuridical%20precedence%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20of%20pooled%20sovereignty%2C%20seen%20as%20foundational%20to%20the%20functioning%20of%20the%20GST%2C%20has%20come%20under%20threat%20due%20to%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20judgment%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fsupremecourt%2F2020%2F23083%2F23083_2020_4_1501_35969_Judgement_19-May-2022.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EUnion%20of%20India%20vs.%20Mohit%20Minerals%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20which%20a%20three-judge%20bench%2C%20presided%20by%20now%20Chief%20Justice%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%2C%20explained%20by%20Gautam%20Bhatia%20recently%2C%20held%20that%20the%20GST%20Council%E2%80%99s%20decisions%20are%20not%20binding%20on%20legislative%20bodies%20and%20that%20both%20Parliament%20and%20state%20legislatures%20possess%20plenary%20powers%20to%20make%20laws%20as%20they%20deem%20fit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20examining%20the%20case%20that%20came%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20the%20bench%20considered%20the%20purport%20of%20Article%20279A%20and%20made%20a%20series%20of%20findings%2C%20explained%20by%20Bhatia%2C%20which%20could%20%E2%80%9Cpotentially%20dismantle%20the%20idea%20of%20GST%20as%20understood%20through%20the%20101st%20amendment%E2%80%9D%20(via%20which%20the%20legal%20way%20for%20creating%20a%20GST%20was%20made%20possible).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20recognised%20that%20the%20GST%20Council%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Crecommendations%E2%80%9D%20cannot%20be%20observed%20as%20binding%20(on%20states)%20since%20it%20would%20violate%20the%20supremacy%20of%20Parliament%20and%20the%20state-legislatures%20since%20both%20have%20been%20afforded%20%E2%80%9Csimultaneous%E2%80%9D%20legislative%20power%20on%20GST.%20Secondly%2C%20the%20virtual%20veto%20given%20to%20the%20Union%20in%20the%20GST%20Council%20would%20lead%20to%20a%20violation%20of%20fiscal%20federalism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20the%20two%20federal%20principles%20discussed%2C%20the%20court%20in%20this%20case%20has%20provided%20a%20strong%20juridical%20precedence%20for%20states%20to%20exercise%20their%20parliamentary%20power%20and%20not%20see%20the%20GST%20Council%E2%80%99s%20recommendations%20as%20binding%2C%20when%20the%20Centre%20refuses%20to%20act%20in%20a%20%E2%80%98reasonable%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98proportionate%E2%80%99%20manner%2C%20in%20its%20own%20devolution%20practice%20for%20either%20political%20or%20any%20other%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2016th%20Finance%20Commission%20must%20address%20and%20resolve%20critical%20issues%20such%20as%20the%20sharing%20of%20resources%20from%20the%20divisible%20pool%20and%20the%20extent%20of%20cesses%20and%20surcharges.%20There%20are%20historical%20wrongs%20in%20vertical%20devolution%20that%20merit%20greater%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20political%20will%20to%20engage%20with%20principles%2C%20due%20process%2C%20and%20constitutional%20morals%2C%20as%20evident%20in%20the%20fiscal%20conduct%20of%20the%20Centre%20%E2%80%93%20which%20has%20put%20political%20means%20over%20anything%20else%20in%20its%20relationship%20with%20states%20and%20other%20institutions%20%E2%80%93%20how%20and%20to%20what%20extent%20the%20Finance%20Commission%20addresses%20these%20issues%20with%20an%20%E2%80%98independent%2C%20non-partisan%20mandate%E2%80%99%20will%20remain%20a%20question%20to%20be%20answered%20on%20its%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDeepanshu%20Mohan%20is%20Professor%20of%20Economics%2C%20Dean%2C%20the%20Office%20of%20Interdisciplinarity%20and%20Director%2C%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%20(CNES)%20at%20O.P.%20Jindal%20Global%20University.%20He%20is%20a%20Visiting%20Professor%20at%20the%20London%20School%20of%20Economics%20and%20Political%20Science%20and%20has%20Visiting%20positions%20at%20University%20of%20London%2C%20University%20of%20Ottawa%2C%20Stellenbosch%20University%20(to%20name%20a%20few).%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709888930000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F08142600%2Fimage-1921.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitical-economy%2Fthe-16th-finance-commission-must-heed-3-principles-to-fix-resource-sharing-between-union-and-states%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Given%20the%20lack%20of%20political%20will%20to%20prioritise%20principles%2C%20due%20process%2C%20and%20constitutional%20integrity%2C%20how%20and%20to%20what%20extent%20the%20Commission%20addresses%20these%20issues%20with%20an%20'independent%2C%20non-partisan%20mandate'%20will%20remain%20a%20question%20requiring%20its%20own%20answer.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitical-economy%2Fthe-16th-finance-commission-must-heed-3-principles-to-fix-resource-sharing-between-union-and-states%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22American%20Constitution%20RIP%3A%20US%20Spiralling%2C%20Crises%20Accelerate%20in%20Critical%20Election%20Year%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F03124308%2F1080px-President_Trump_Travels_to_Arizona_50040937841.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20ruled%20that%20former%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20may%20stand%20for%20election%20in%20every%20state%20across%20the%20country%20and%20that%20the%20penalty%20for%20insurrection%20against%20the%20US%20state%20is%20a%20matter%20for%20politicians%20in%20Congress%2C%20not%20the%20courts.%20Those%20politicians%20had%20already%20decided%20in%202021%20by%20majorities%20in%20both%20House%20of%20Representatives%20and%20the%20US%20Senate%20that%20Trump%20was%20guilty%20of%20insurrection%20on%20January%206%2C%202021%2C%20when%20a%20mob%20of%20his%20supporters%20stormed%20the%20Capitol%2C%20causing%20the%20death%20and%20injury%20of%20several%20people.%20But%20the%20Biden%20administration%20failed%20to%20bring%20such%20a%20charge%20against%20Trump%2C%20and%20dragged%20its%20feet%20on%20other%20charges%20of%20election%20interference%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20effectively%20appeased%20Trumpism%20and%20the%20far%20right%20and%20are%20paying%20the%20price%2C%20as%20will%20the%20American%20people.%20And%20given%20that%20the%20United%20States%20remains%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20pivotal%20state%2C%20so%20will%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20ruling%20thus%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20went%20well%20beyond%20the%20immediacies%20of%20the%20Colorado%20court%20decision%20to%20bar%20Trump%20from%20the%20ballot%20in%20that%20state.%20The%20national%20court%20did%20not%20merely%20strike%20down%20the%20Colorado%20decision%2C%20it%20kicked%20the%20issue%20to%20the%20Congress%2C%20made%20it%20their%20job%20to%20decide%20the%20outcome%2C%20making%20it%20an%20overtly%20political%20decision%20they%20must%20know%20will%20never%20emerge%20from%20the%20current%20Congress%20of%20far%20right%20do%20nothings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20now%20has%20a%20free%20pass%2C%20a%20virtual%20%E2%80%98get%20out%20of%20jail%20free%E2%80%99%20card.%20The%20appetite%20for%20democracy%2C%20constitutional%20norms%2C%20and%20checks%20and%20balances%20among%20US%20elites%20is%20dying.%20It%20only%20just%20made%20it%20through%20on%20January%206%2C%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWill%20it%20scrape%20through%20in%20January%202025%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20majority%20corrupt%20right%20wing%20court%2C%20with%20liberal%20accomplices%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Supreme%20Court%20that%20just%20ruled%20has%20three%20justices%20appointed%20by%20Trump%20(Barrett%2C%20Gorsuch%2C%20Kavanaugh)%2C%20two%20appointed%20by%20George%20W.%20Bush%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20contested%20election%20of%202000%20(Alito%2C%20Roberts)%2C%20and%20the%20controversial%20Clarence%20Thomas%20whose%20wife%20(Ginni%20Thomas)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbsnews.com%2Fsanfrancisco%2Fnews%2Fginni-thomas-tells-jan-6-committee-she-regrets-texting-with-meadows-about-2020-election%2F%5C%22%3Eplayed%20a%20key%20role%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Trump%E2%80%99s%20failed%20bid%20to%20overturn%20the%202020%20election.%20The%20standing%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20fallen%20through%20the%20floor%20due%20to%20well%20documented%20levels%20of%20corruption.%20Supreme%20Court%20justices%20are%20subject%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brennancenter.org%2Four-work%2Fanalysis-opinion%2Fnew-supreme-court-ethics-code-designed-fail%5C%22%3Eno%20independently-policed%20ethical%20code%20of%20conduct%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20cannot%20easily%20be%20removed%20from%20their%20position.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPreviously%2C%20when%20Trump%20had%20asked%20the%20SC%20to%20rule%20on%20whether%20as%20president%20he%20was%20exempt%20from%20all%20laws%2C%20the%20SC%20decided%20it%20%3Cem%3Ewas%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20matter%20for%20the%20courts%20but%20sent%20the%20case%20to%20an%20appeals%20court.%20When%20the%20latter%20ruled%20against%20Trump%20in%20the%20starkest%20terms%2C%20the%20SC%20decided%20to%20take%20the%20case%20but%20not%20until%20the%20end%20of%20April%2C%20causing%20further%20delay%20in%20a%20key%20year.%20This%20delay%20virtually%20guarantees%20there%20will%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2Ff450d649-6449-4c2d-87fd-b608dfd9c500%5C%22%3Eno%20trials%20as%20such%20for%20months%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20the%20SC%E2%80%99s%20ruling%20may%20not%20be%20available%20until%20the%20summer.%C2%A0Trump%20may%20get%20what%20he%E2%80%99s%20wanted%20all%20along%3A%20to%20drag%20out%20proceedings%20until%20after%20the%20election%20which%2C%20should%20he%20win%2C%20he%20would%20undoubtedly%20dismiss%20as%20the%20workings%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98deep%20state%E2%80%99%20against%20a%20man%20of%20the%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20SC%20has%2C%20therefore%2C%20presented%20Trump%20and%20the%20GOP%20immunity%20from%20laws%20and%20constitutional%20norms.%20Those%20Trump-inspired%20insurrectionists%20of%20January%206%2C%202021%20are%20free%20to%20run%20for%20future%20office%20%E2%80%93%20and%20a%20large%20number%20of%20them%20have%20been%20sitting%20in%20the%20House%20and%20Senate%20since%20then%20in%20any%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Republican%20party%20%E2%80%93%20a%20full-fledged%20far%20right%20party%20%E2%80%93%20is%20now%20above%20the%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20%E2%80%98Super%20Tuesday%E2%80%99%2C%20and%20the%20suspension%20by%20Nikki%20Haley%20of%20her%20campaign%2C%20Trump%20is%20guaranteed%20to%20win%20the%20Republican%20party%20nomination%20for%20the%20presidential%20election%20in%20November.%20More%2C%20he%20leads%20in%20several%20national%20opinion%20polls%20against%20his%20Democratic%20incumbent%2C%20President%20Joe%20Biden.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20in%20the%20position%20that%2C%20should%20Trump%20emerge%20victorious%20in%20November%2C%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20so-called%20free%20world%20faces%20the%20prospect%20of%20governing%20from%20prison%2C%20were%20the%20justice%20system%20to%20take%20its%20normal%20course.%20But%20there%20is%20nothing%20normal%20about%20our%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBiden%20administration%20on%20the%20ropes%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJoseph%20Biden%20reportedly%20decided%20to%20come%20out%20of%20retirement%20and%20run%20against%20Trump%20in%202020%20after%20pro-Trump%20neo-Nazis%20and%20white%20supremacists%20rioted%20in%20Charlottesville%20in%202017%2C%20killing%20a%20counter-protestor.%20Biden%20wanted%20to%20fight%20for%20the%20%E2%80%98soul%E2%80%99%20of%20America%2C%20be%20its%20saviour%20in%20time%20of%20national%20need.%20Instead%2C%20he%20may%20well%20be%20the%20lead%20actor%20in%20a%20tragedy%20%E2%80%93%20the%20saviour%20who%20paves%20the%20way%20for%20Trump%20II%2C%20a%20newly-emboldened%20and%20revived%20leader%20swearing%20vengeance%20on%20his%20opponents%20and%20a%20dictatorship%20to%20boot.%20Close%20the%20borders%2C%20deport%20millions%20of%20immigrants%2C%20burn%20down%20regulation%20of%20oil%20and%20gas%2C%20free%20the%20corporations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERacist%20divide-and-rule%20coupled%20with%20complete%20freedom%20for%20corporations%2C%20whose%20executives%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2Ff450d649-6449-4c2d-87fd-b608dfd9c500%5C%22%3Econtinue%20to%20back%3C%2Fa%3E%20Trump%20and%20the%20far%20right%20GOP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBiden%20has%20coupled%20his%20disastrous%20appeasement%20of%20Trump%20and%20the%20GOP%20with%20an%20equally%20disastrous%20foreign%20policy.%20He%20now%20faces%20a%20political%20backlash%20related%20to%20his%20administration%E2%80%99s%20military%2C%20financial%20and%20diplomatic%20support%20for%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20horrific%20war%20on%20Gaza.%20Biden%20is%20alienating%2C%20according%20to%20reliable%20polls%2C%20two%20key%20constituencies%20that%20may%20render%20him%20a%20one-term%20president%3A%20Arab%20and%20Muslim%20Americans%2C%20and%20younger%20voters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20a%20tiny%20percentage%20of%20the%20US%20electorate%2C%20Muslim%20Americans%20could%20be%20the%20margin%20in%20key%20states%20that%20swings%20the%20election%20for%20Trump%2C%20even%20if%20they%20stay%20home.%20This%20is%20especially%20the%20case%20in%20states%20such%20as%20Michigan%20but%20also%20Georgia%20and%20Pennsylvania.%20Arab%20and%20Muslim%20American%20voters%20overwhelmingly%20supported%20Biden%20against%20the%20Islamophobic%20Trump%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYounger%20voters%2C%20a%20far%20larger%20section%20of%20the%20Democratic%20party%E2%80%99s%20voter%20base%2C%20are%20also%20vexed%20by%20Biden%E2%80%99s%20Israel-Gaza%20policies%20and%20opposition%20to%20a%20ceasefire.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3EAmericans%E2%80%99%20choice%3A%20Anger%20vs%20fear%2C%20not%20democracy%20vs%20dictatorship%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20what%20does%20all%20this%20boil%20down%20to%20in%20this%20critical%20election%20year%3F%20What%20are%20the%20options%20for%20voters%3F%20In%20the%20end%2C%20it%20would%20appear%20that%20Americans%20must%20decide%20if%20their%20anger%20and%20frustrations%20with%20the%20Biden%20administration%20outweigh%20their%20fear%20of%20a%20Trump%20second%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20suspect%20that%20the%20Biden%20administration%20is%20(if%20increasingly%20anxiously)%20satisfied%20that%20Trump%20is%20their%20opponent%20for%20the%20White%20House.%20Indeed%2C%20that%20was%20always%20the%20plan.%20Fear%20of%20Trump%20may%20ultimately%2C%20in%20the%20privacy%20of%20the%20voting%20booth%2C%20drive%20voters%20into%20Democrats%E2%80%99%20arms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20fitting%20might%20that%20be%3A%20Trump%20who%20used%20fear%20so%20skilfully%20in%202016%20is%20the%20unwitting%20author%20of%20his%20own%20downfall.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Biden%E2%80%99s%20strategy%20of%20appeasement%20may%20well%20backfire.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fiparmar%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EInderjeet%20Parmar%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20professor%20of%20international%20politics%20and%20associate%20dean%20of%20research%20in%20the%20School%20of%20Policy%20and%20Global%20Affairs%20at%20City%2C%20University%20of%20London%2C%20a%20fellow%20of%20the%20Academy%20of%20Social%20Sciences%2C%20and%20a%20columnist%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Wire%3Cem%3E.%20He%20is%20an%20International%20Fellow%20at%20the%20ROADS%20Initiative%20think%20tank%2C%20Islamabad%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3Eand%20author%20of%20several%20books%20including%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EFoundations%20of%20the%20American%20Century%3Cem%3E.%20He%20is%20currently%20writing%20a%20book%20on%20the%20history%2C%20politics%2C%20and%20powers%20of%20the%20US%20Foreign%20Policy%20Establishment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E